        // --- Tutorial ---
        'tutorial_title_main': 'Most Important Things',
        'tutorial_intro': 'Read the following carefully to pass the pirate exam!',
        'tutorial_acc_credit_title': 'A New Literary Ecosystem',
        'tutorial_acc_credit_body': 'Abrigo is not just scenery; it is a fantasy and sci-fi universe crafted with high literary ambition, where the grotesque reality of society cuts as sharply as cinematic, high-tension action. In this world, classical philosophies and the quiet wisdom of Taoism collide with Lovecraftian mystery and King-like atmosphere. Characters are never cardboard figures: they are flesh-and-blood people with personal histories and distinct speech rooted in their social background. The chronicles of Abrigo are unashamedly explicit about life in full: people eat, sleep, excrete, have sex, fail, get sick, and die. The narrative moves with dramaturgical precision from wide perspective to concrete detail, while viewpoint shifts and a non-linear timeline challenge the reader to assemble the whole from scattered fragments.<br/>The world of Abrigo is never static: a background program builds each expedition from unique ideas. The game improves itself through interactions and feedback, and its characters keep maturing, offering players more advanced assistance and increasingly refined communication. You do not just read here; you become part of a self-learning, pulsating literary evolution.',
        'tutorial_acc_scroll_title': 'Where Reality and Imagination Forge a New Alliance',
        'tutorial_acc_scroll_body': 'In this environment, the Hungarian e-book is reborn. Abrigo is an exclusive platform where every text carries unique hidden coding, making illegal distribution traceable back to its source. At the same time, the system has broken free from rigid publishing constraints: authors and publishers can update and expand works at any time, and changes become instantly available to every owner. It is also a community game: players form reading circles, launch expeditions for rare finds, and receive commission measured in Talentum for active promotion and community effort. Whether through solo action or teamwork, free reading and growth opportunities remain open to everyone.',
        'tutorial_acc_market_title': 'Where the Story Comes Alive',
        'tutorial_acc_market_body': 'For aspiring writers, the system offers a full arsenal of opportunities: in the smoky depths of the Tavern, expert beta readers support first attempts, while in the silence of the Cloud Monastery, wise monks, designers, and translators polish future publications to final form. For publishers, this is low-risk future ground: real demand can be measured here, new names are born here, and campaign launches can begin here as the antechamber of print success. In this continuously self-learning and evolving universe, no two adventures are the same; characters mature through experience, and dialogues reflect origin and destiny. Step in as well: where one story ends, the true journey begins.',
        'tutorial_acc_world_title': 'About the world',
        'tutorial_acc_world_body': 'In the world of Abrigo, the secret pirate harbor is called Hebok. Here you can find the Market, the Book Shrine, and the Tavern among many other buildings. You can read detailed descriptions on each location info panel. In the Harbor you can rent ships, and in the Shipyard you can have your own ships built, even from custom plans. In the Tavern you can hire a crew, or you can join someone else as a team member. The key is to gather as many books as possible, because that is what defines rank and wealth here.',
        'tutorial_acc_money_title': 'Currencies',
        'tutorial_acc_money_body': 'In the game we use Pirate Credit and Talentum.<ul><li>You can earn Pirate Credit through adventures or beta reading jobs from the Tavern. You can also take a loan if the Bank grants one. On the Market, you can turn almost anything into money except your sanctified books.</li><li>You can get Talentum by supporting us on Patreon or by sending a friendly PayPal donation. We thank you with Talentum. If you are lucky enough to find a spirit crystal, the Book Shrine pays in Talentum, and you can also offer valuable items on the Market for Talentum.</li><li>In the Bank you can exchange Talentum to Pirate Credit, but there is no reverse exchange.</li></ul>',
        'tutorial_acc_hartya_title': 'Processing Hartya',
        'tutorial_acc_hartya_body': '<ul><li>Hartya by itself is not yet readable material. The Scrollmaster handles it in bundles of 30: either he pays 1 Pirate Credit for 30 Hartya, or you pay 11 Pirate Credit and he presses your 30 Hartya into one readable scroll.</li><li>You can sell scrolls, trade them, hand them in to the Scrollmaster for 10 Pirate Credit, or collect all parts of a book and stitch them into one full copy.</li><li>A copy contains the full story and can be sanctified into a Book in the Book Shrine. Copies also fuel expeditions, and you can even put your own copy into play.</li></ul>',
        'tutorial_acc_book_title': 'Book',
        'tutorial_acc_book_body': 'The Book is the core sacred value in the world of Abrigo. If you have a copy, the Book Shrine can sanctify it into a Book for Talentum. You can dedicate the Book to someone else, which is a huge gift, and sanctification also grants ten new copies. After sanctification, the Book becomes downloadable as an eBook and is permanently bound to its owner.<br><br>Because of this, the Book cannot be sold or redistributed later. If it appears in illegal places, the owner is held responsible: the Book loses value, no more copy commissions are paid, and the Book is sent to the Book Prison.',
        'tutorial_acc_rank_title': 'Rank',
        'tutorial_acc_rank_body': 'In Abrigo, rank depends on the size of your library. For example, below 130 books do not expect to be accepted as a captain, even with a full fleet. But if you somehow obtain two spirit crystals, even kings will welcome you to their table. That is why joining spirit crystal expeditions is often a life-or-death struggle.',
        'tutorial_acc_library_title': 'The library',
        'tutorial_acc_library_body': 'You can read your acquired Scrolls, Copies, Maps, and Ship Logs in your Library. You can also download your existing Books here and save them to any other device. If you want to make a copy of one of your maps, you must walk over to the Copy Workshop. If you want to expand your ship log, that should happen strictly on the ship. It is a tradition.',
        'tutorial_acc_mapslogs_title': 'Maps and ship logs',
        'tutorial_acc_mapslogs_body': 'Although not in the same category as Books, a detailed map or a heavily annotated ship log can be extremely valuable. Since there are no fixed modules in the game, most treasures are found based on these notes and maps. Most expeditions start because of discovered ship logs mentioning copies, crystal books, or even spirit crystal locations.',
